(1) Any person introducing and importing gold from any place beyond the boundaries of Zambia shall, by written notice, inform the Controller of Customs and Excise or other proper official of the fact that he is so introducing such gold , and shall make a solemn declaration before such official stating— (a) the place from which such gold was obtained; (b) the date on which it was obtained; (c) the name and usual address of the person from whom and the manner in which it was obtained; (d) the weight and value of such gold and whether the same is gold itself refined or unrefined, or amalgam of gold , or slimes or scrapings.
