(2) Any person who shall make a declaration which is to his knowledge false and untrue in any of the above particulars shall be deemed to have contravened subsection (1) and shall, upon conviction thereof, be liable to all the penalties which may be inflicted on any person who commits perjury, and the gold introduced and imported shall be confiscated.
